Chapter 1.7

Waking up at exactly five o’clock, Zhou Yunsheng instinctively tightened his embrace around the warm body beside him. The man’s hair was messy, and his sharp, handsome features radiated a lazy satisfaction after intimate moments. His eyes, which always gleamed with a dangerous light, were tightly closed at this moment, tempting Zhou Yunsheng to lean down and kiss him.

As a villain controlled by a system, and with a pure gay attribute, Zhou Yunsheng's previous days had not been easy. He was often forced to "fall in love" with certain people, even engaging in the most intimate of actions. Every time this happened, the system would take control of his body. Many times, when he woke up and saw the female protagonist either angrily scolding him, attempting to kill herself, or planning to take them both down together, he actually wanted to yell at her even more, to seek death and despair even more, and to take them both down together even more than she did.

The past was too painful to look back on. Zhou Yunsheng pinched the man’s sexy and determined jaw, kissing him deeply.

Du Xulang had already woken up the moment his lover opened his eyes. But he knew his lover had a habit of gazing at him for a long time before getting out of bed, then giving him a kiss full of intense emotion. His lover’s appearance was handsome and gentle, always carrying a faint smile at the corner of his lips. But after getting to know him, one would realize that he had a very strong personality.

This led to their intimate moments often resembling a battle for control, intense, passionate, and fulfilling. Once he experienced it, he couldn’t get enough.

He chuckled softly, grabbing his lover’s flexible waist and pressing back... His attitude toward this relationship had never been more serious. Initially, he hadn’t thought about forever, but as time passed, his lover's appearance went from youthful to mature, gradually blooming with a dazzling radiance, making his thoughts linger on him for a long time. He suddenly realized that maybe he should do something to permanently keep him, to possess him honorably.

Zhou Yunsheng didn’t know what Du Xulang was thinking. He only felt that the man was particularly excited today and didn’t stop for more than two hours in bed. Fortunately, his body had been modified; otherwise, his waist would have broken.

They showered together and were about to order takeout when Zhou Yunsheng’s phone rang. He glanced at the caller ID, and his brow involuntarily raised—it was Zhou Wen'ang.

"Okay, I’ll be right back." After silently listening to the call, he threw the phone aside and started packing his bags.

"What’s wrong?" Du Xulang felt that his lover's expression was a bit off.

"Zhou Hao is dying; he wants me to come back." Zhou Yunsheng answered without looking up, his face showing no sadness over the impending death of a family member, only anticipation and amusement. He glanced at the smart wristband on his wrist. The progress bar at the top left corner had remained at 50% since he founded Noah Universe, and it hadn't changed since then.

And Zhou Hao’s death was the tragic turning point in the original host's life. Only by destroying this period of time could he completely disrupt the world’s development.

He stuck out his tongue and licked his lips, suddenly feeling a surge of excitement—uncontrollable excitement.

They packed their bags and booked flights, arriving at the Zhou family home that evening.

"Big brother, you're back!" Zhou Wen'ang hurriedly greeted, embracing his long-lost brother tightly, his eyes red and glistening with tears. If it weren’t for Du Xulang's investigation, he might have been fooled by the excellent acting.

"Where's dad?" Zhou Yunsheng pushed him aside, his expression calm, his tone even somewhat indifferent. It wasn't that he couldn't act; it was just that with the power to crush his opponents, he no longer bothered to disguise his feelings.

"He's upstairs. The doctor said he won't survive tonight, so I brought him home. He felt uneasy lying in the hospital." Zhou Wen'ang spoke as he led them upstairs, casually asking, "By the way, why is Assistant Du here? Did you meet abroad?"

Before Zhou Yunsheng could answer, Du Xulang spoke slowly, "It wasn’t by chance. We’re currently in a relationship. I’m Yunsheng’s boyfriend."

To come out to his father-in-law on the brink of death... Du Xulang must be planning to make him die with regret! Wait, why is it father-in-law and not father? Zhou Yunsheng silently complained in his heart, his cold eyes finally lighting up with a smile, nodding in agreement.

Zhou Wen'ang almost missed a step and nearly fell down the stairs. Fortunately, the old butler beside him steadied him.

"You go ahead. I'll wait outside." When they reached the door, Du Xulang had no intention of entering to visit.

Zhou Yunsheng wasn’t bothered. He touched his handsome face, then strolled inside. The dimly lit room was filled with the smell of medicine and the ominous atmosphere of impending death. Zhou Hao was covered in tubes, his thin chest barely rising.

"Dad, Big Brother's back." Zhou Wen'ang shouted a couple of times near Zhou's father’s ear. Seeing that he didn’t respond, he was almost eager to drag Zhou Yunsheng out.

"Yunsheng’s back?" As they were about to leave the room, Zhou’s father suddenly woke up, struggling to speak. "Yunsheng, I’m sorry, I’m sorry for your mother. It was I who caused her death..."

"Dad, those things are in the past. We don’t blame you. Mom couldn’t handle it herself, it had nothing to do with you. Don’t worry, don’t think too much." Zhou Wen'ang quickly rushed to the bedside and pinched Zhou’s father’s fingers forcefully. They say that when someone is about to die, their words are good, and when Zhou’s father strongly insisted on having Zhou Yunsheng called back, Zhou Wen'ang sensed that Zhou’s father might reveal the truth about the past.

He had already come this far, with only one step left. How could he let his years of planning fail?

Zhou’s father winced in pain. Seeing the pleading look in his younger son’s eyes, he finally decided to take the secret to his grave. When Zhou's father fell back into unconsciousness and couldn’t be awakened no matter what, Zhou Wen'ang secretly breathed a sigh of relief.

Zhou Yunsheng stood three meters away, watching with a mocking smile on his lips.

Meanwhile, Zhou Wenjing hurriedly arrived at the Zhou family home, and was startled to find his uncle there.

"I'll explain later. Do you want to go in and see?" Du Xulang pointed toward the bedroom door with a cigarette between his fingers, while heading toward the study next door, blatantly eavesdropping.

Zhou Father's bedroom and the study were connected by a thin door. Sitting in the study, one could clearly hear the noise coming from the other side. Zhou Wenjing hesitated for a moment before following him into the room.

Zhou Yunsheng's hearing was far superior to ordinary people, so he naturally heard their footsteps but paid no attention. He sat on the single sofa beside the bed, casually speaking, "Why did Father say sorry to me? Because he murdered my mother?"

Zhou Father suddenly opened his eyes and began to cough violently.

Zhou Wenang barely suppressed his panic. While helping Zhou Father pat his chest, he scolded, "Big Brother, what nonsense are you talking about? Mom committed suicide."

"What right do you have to call her 'Mom'? Are you her son?" Zhou Yunsheng leaned comfortably back in his chair, crossing his long legs.

Zhou Wenang's face twisted in anger. The two people eavesdropping next door also couldn't help but breathe more heavily. The heart monitor emitted a long beep before stopping completely. Zhou Father was scared to death. But no one in the room moved or even glanced in his direction. At this point, Zhou Wenang gave up his pretense, slowly sat down across from Zhou Yunsheng, pushed his hair back, revealing a face full of hostility.

"How did you know?"

"Your thumb gave you away." Zhou Yunsheng sneered. "Your thumb is missing a segment, it's short and bald, very ugly, just like that woman. It's a dominant gene that will definitely be passed on to the next generation. But Mom and Zhou Hao both have normal hands. I don't need to explain what that means, right?"

Zhou Wenang forcefully bent his thumb, and after a long while, he laughed lowly. "So what if you know? You can't do anything to me now. The Zhou family is mine. Oh, right, you can try to get Yang Xi's inheritance back or beg the Yang family to deal with me. But unfortunately, you probably don't know yet, the Yang Group is currently undertaking the underwater tunnel project between Qindao City and Rongcheng, and the Zhou Group has promised to invest 2 billion in the Yang family. If the Zhou family withdraws the investment, the Yang family will go bankrupt, completely."

As if he found his words amusing, Zhou Wenang's low laugh turned into a loud one. The days of living in fear would finally be over once the Yang Group collapsed, how could he not feel elated?

But Zhou Yunsheng's reaction disappointed him. The young man still sat steadily, waiting for him to finish laughing before asking, "So, did Zhou Hao kill my mother?"

"Guess," Zhou Wenang cleverly didn't respond.

"You've been trying to deal with me all these years, right? That poisoned cigarette that Elsa gave me was actually meant for me?"

"Such a pity." Zhou Wenang smiled ambiguously. At critical moments, he wouldn't allow the other person to catch any dirt on him, trying to bait him into making a confession and secretly recording it—no chance.

Zhou Yunsheng also smiled, walking over and patting Zhou Wenang's cheek gently, his tone exceedingly tender, "Enjoy this final celebration, my dear brother." With that, he opened the door and left.

The two people in the study were struggling to digest the bombshell they had just overheard. Du Xulang recalled another illegitimate child of the Zhou family who had died, remembering that the birth dates of the two children were very similar, and finally piecing together many suspicious details. To see through such a perfect scam—Yunsheng's insight was terrifying. When did he discover it? What did he feel at that time? His father killed his mother, and his own brother turned out to be his enemy's child—what kind of emotions did he experience as he made his way to this point?

No wonder he felt no affection for Zhou Hao, no wonder his attitude toward Zhou Wenang had changed so dramatically. Du Xulang's heart ached unbearably.

Zhou Wenjing also had a very ugly expression. He had never expected that the person he had been guarding against for years was not his real enemy. All the kindness, comfort, and gifts... they were all fake. All these years, he had been like a fool, played with by Zhou Wenang, while Zhou Father never once mentioned him.

At this moment, he wished he could strangle Zhou Wenang. When his anger subsided, he walked toward Zhou Yunsheng's room. The servants were coming and going, systematically preparing for the upcoming funeral.

"Your mother wasn't driven to death by my mother." After knocking on the door, he spoke bluntly.

Zhou Yunsheng raised an eyebrow.

"So I don't owe you anything." Zhou Wenjing had to admit he felt relieved when he said this. His feelings for Zhou Yunsheng were complicated. The hatred accumulated over more than ten years couldn't be completely erased, but he also felt sorry for him.

"What do you mean?" Zhou Yunsheng patiently pressed.

"I just want to tell you that I won't take revenge on you, but I also won't help you. From now on, you're on your own." Because Zhou Yunsheng had always kept a low profile, Zhou Wenjing had always thought he was a penniless student. Now, with billions to his name, Zhou Wenjing naturally looked down on him.

The humiliation Zhou Yunsheng had inflicted on him back then was something he could never forget. Now, sparing him out of pity was already the greatest mercy, and he couldn't ask for more.

He said these things to avoid the day when his identity as the president of the Zongda Group and the nephew of the Du family head would be exposed, and Zhou Yunsheng would shamelessly cling to him. He naturally assumed that his uncle would appear at the Zhou family to support him.

Zhou Yunsheng was a bit speechless. Zhou Wenjing stared at him for a while, then turned and left.

"Is he too full of himself? What was that expression and tone? Does he think I'm a pitiful stray dog? That not making things worse for me is his biggest help?" Zhou Yunsheng grabbed Du Xulang's tie and pulled it tight.

Du Xulang hurriedly held his lover's waist and sincerely apologized. "It's my fault, I didn't teach him well. Babe, let's talk in bed."

Zhou Yunsheng: "..."

It seemed that everyone had forgotten to mourn for Zhou Father's passing.


——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————


Chapter 1.8

The funeral of Mr. Zhou was both grand and hurried. After lying in state for three days, the burial took place in a rush. On the second day of the funeral, the lawyer brought Mr. Zhou’s will, which shocked everyone. Mr. Zhou bequeathed all his property, including 30% of Zhou Group's shares, to his youngest son, Zhou Wen'ang, while his eldest and second sons received nothing.

The second son, Zhou Wenjing, was an illegitimate child and had never been favored by Mr. Zhou. It was not surprising that he did not inherit anything, but what was strange was that even the eldest son received nothing. When it was revealed that even Mrs. Zhou’s inheritance was entirely left to the youngest son, people could not help but comment on how biased the Zhou couple was. How would Zhou Yunsheng, who had no assets, live in the future? Had they not considered this?

“Mr. Zhou, please sign.” The lawyer placed a thick stack of documents in front of Zhou Wen'ang for him to sign, and the others could only stare blankly.

“This is impossible. How could Zhou Hao leave nothing for Yunsheng? He had said before he passed that he would leave Zhou Group to Yunsheng.” Old Lady Yang shouted in disbelief, while Mr. Yang looked at his jubilant grandson with a look of doubt. As in-laws, they were invited to the will reading.

Zhou Yunsheng smiled and patted his grandmother’s aging hand. Although their relationship had grown distant, the care the elderly couple had shown him had never changed.

“How could it be impossible? He has been abroad for six or seven years, and never even called home. It was I who stayed by Dad’s side and helped manage the company. Isn’t it natural that Dad left the inheritance to me?” Zhou Wen'ang no longer showed the previous respect for the elderly couple.

“But Xi’er’s inheritance was already given to you. Your elder brother has nothing. How will he live in the future...” Old Lady Yang still felt it was very unfair.

“Whether he lives or dies has nothing to do with me. It’s getting late. Please leave. Oh, and starting tomorrow, I will be the new president of Zhou Group. I’ve decided to withdraw investments from Yang Group, so please be prepared.” Zhou Wen'ang smiled with a fake grin as he urged them to leave.

“You brat, what are you saying? Do you know the consequences of withdrawing investments from Yang Group? Do you want to bankrupt Yang Group?” Mr. Yang asked in a deep voice, his brows furrowed with anger. He could not believe that his grandson, whom he had once thought so filial, could be so heartless. What had the Yang family ever done to him to deserve such treatment?

Zhou Wenjing, who had been expressionless all along, finally showed his first smile in days. He knew that the will had nothing to do with him. He had come today purely to watch the drama. The Yang family had never respected him, and now, seeing Zhou Wen'ang tear his face with the man who had been cherished for twenty years, it was truly a case of “dog biting dog.”

Zhou Yunsheng remained composed throughout, patting his grandfather’s shoulder lightly, and smiled, “Let him withdraw his investments. Grandfather, grandmother, let's go.”

“But…” How could Mr. Yang leave? If Zhou Group withdrew investments, the underwater tunnel project of Yang Group would face a huge cash shortage, causing the project to be delayed, or even abandoned. In such a case, not only would Yang Group’s initial investment of over 10 billion be lost, but they would also have to pay huge breach of contract fines and bank loans. Selling off all the assets under Yang Group wouldn’t even cover the hole.

Zhou Wen'ang was trying to destroy the Yang family!

“Even if you beg him, he won’t change his mind. What he wants is for Yang Group to be destroyed. Grandfather, grandmother, come with me, I have a way,” Zhou Yunsheng feared that speaking too directly would upset the elderly couple, so he firmly led them away.

"You have a way? What way do you have?" Zhou Wen'ang and Zhou Wenjing both scoffed internally.

As soon as Mr. Zhou passed away, the cooperative relationship between Zhou Group and Yang Group collapsed. The new president of Zhou Group, Zhou Wen'ang, announced that he would withdraw investments from Yang Group’s underwater tunnel project, with no explanation given. Yang Group was facing its biggest crisis, and if not handled properly, they would be on the verge of bankruptcy.

However, no one extended a helping hand. Everyone was waiting for Yang Group to collapse so they could take over the underwater tunnel project, which was expected to generate hundreds of billions in profits, at a minimal price. This was the nature of business—driven by profit, where friends and even family could be betrayed.

But what was surprising was that Mr. Yang seemed remarkably calm. He returned home, ate as usual, slept as usual, and showed no signs of the panic the outside world expected. The Yang family's children also seemed unfazed. Yang Zhenhai, the current head of the family, had even spent millions on jewelry, showing no sign of financial trouble.

“Oh, my nephew is the president of Noah Universal, why should I worry? Do you know Noah Universal? It’s ranked first in the Fortune 500,” Mrs. Yang said, staring at the large diamond ring on her finger, smiling brightly.

The sales assistant responded obediently, but thought to herself, You have two nephews. One inherited Zhou Group, and the other is a penniless nobody. How can you have another nephew who is the world’s wealthiest? Dream on.

Although the Yang family's reaction was strange, Zhou Wen'ang had no time to care. He was under attack by Zhou Wenjing. He never imagined that the illegitimate son he once manipulated would now be a billionaire, hoping to compete with him for Zhou Group.

Zhou Wenjing first spread the news that Zhou Wen'ang was not the biological son of Yang Xi, then hinted that Zhou Hao had murdered Yang Xi and was after his inheritance. He also publicly released the DNA comparison between Yang Xi and Zhou Wen'ang, prompting the police to launch an investigation. The two scandals shook the public, and Zhou Group’s stock, which had already dropped after Mr. Zhou’s death, hit the limit down.

Meanwhile, Zhou Wenjing took this opportunity to acquire scattered shares, quickly becoming the largest shareholder of Zhou Group.

Zhou Yunsheng, however, remained unshaken. His goal was for the two of them to fight to the death. He never intended to fight Zhou Wen'ang in court for the inheritance; from the start, he decided to make sure they both ended up with nothing. As for Zhou Wenjing, once the biggest winner, he was about to teach him a practical lesson in what it meant to be the “mantis stalking the cicada, unaware of the yellow bird behind.” This would be a lesson in futility.

The despair, heartbreak, and helplessness that Zhou Yunsheng had once endured would never happen again.
After several months, the rivalry between the two brothers of the Zhou family had escalated to a boiling point. Both of them currently held 30% of the shares of Zhou Corporation, and all the shareholders they could persuade had already chosen sides. The final 15% of the shares, which would decide the outcome, were surprisingly in the hands of the head of the Du family.

Seven years ago, he had already become a shareholder of Zhou Corporation, but no one had noticed. Zhou Wen'ang was too preoccupied with other matters to consider the implications of this move by the head of the Du family. He only knew that if he could convince him to sell the shares to him, or to support him at the shareholders' meeting, he would be the ultimate winner.

Unfortunately, Zhou Wenjing and he seemed to have a telepathic connection. As soon as they stepped out of the elevator, the two of them met in the corridor.

"Please come in. Coffee or green tea?" Inoue Hideyama, speaking fluent Mandarin, led them into the CEO's office.

"Coffee (Green tea)." Their answers were completely opposite.

The leather chair swiveled around, and a tall, imposing man with sharp features was sitting there, smoking a cigar, his hair slicked back, revealing a handsome yet devilish face. He exhaled a cloud of smoke, but the sharp gleam in his dark eyes could not be concealed.

Zhou Wenjing sat upright as usual, but Zhou Wen'ang, startled, knocked over his hot coffee. What alarmed him more than the man's identity was Zhou Wenjing's respectful address—he had called the man "uncle!"

"Well, you two are teaming up against me," Zhou Wen'ang muttered, knowing that staying any longer would only lead to humiliation. He covered his burned hand and stormed out.

When he said "teaming up," he was referring to Zhou Wenjing, Zhou Yunsheng, and Du Xulang joining forces, as he knew that Du Xulang was Zhou Yunsheng's boyfriend. With such an influential figure on their side, it was no wonder that the Yang family had raised 2 billion yuan in the shortest time to fill the gap.

However, Zhou Wenjing did not know the full story and thought he was talking about himself and his uncle teaming up. After Zhou Wen'ang left, he affectionately said, "Uncle, do you still want that 15% of the shares? If not, sell them to me, I'll offer a discount."

Du Xulang did not respond immediately but instead asked, "Wenjing, have you ever thought that Zhou Corporation was meant to belong to Yunsheng?"

Zhou Wenjing suppressed his inner hatred and forced a cheerful smile. "Uncle, you once taught me that business is like a battlefield, and if you want something, you have to fight for it. As the saying goes, survival of the fittest, if he wants Zhou Corporation, he can come and compete with me, and we'll see who has the ability."

Du Xulang’s inexplicable support for Zhou Yunsheng made Zhou Wenjing feel a sense of danger.

After a brief silence, Du Xulang nodded. "You're right. Survival of the fittest, whoever has the ability, Zhou Corporation belongs to them."

"So, you’ll just watch and not intervene?" Zhou Wenjing, still feeling uneasy, asked.

"I won't intervene."

"As for the shares..." Zhou Wenjing pressed further. He was afraid that his uncle might give the shares to Zhou Yunsheng. Not confronting Zhou Yunsheng didn’t mean he would let him have it easy. He had already sworn to make him lose everything.

"I'll sell you the 15% shares at 35 yuan per share," Du Xulang offered a reasonable price.

Zhou Wenjing was pleased and immediately took out a check to fill in the numbers. Inoue Hideyama escorted the young man to the elevator, watching his smug face disappear behind the doors. He couldn't help but sigh. "Foolish child, he doesn't even know he's being played by the boss. He thinks the boss's refusal to help everyone is fairness, but in reality, it's just to cover up his bias. With his style, if he acts, it’ll definitely be a storm of blood."

He didn’t compete for the shares of Zhou Corporation not because he lacked the ability, but because he had already planned to destroy Zhou Corporation. Even if he got his hands on those 15% shares, they would eventually become useless.

The boss knew the truth, but for the sake of his lover’s plan, he said nothing and sold a pile of worthless shares to his nephew at an exorbitant price. He really is heartless when it comes to the opposite sex—oh wait, not just the opposite sex, but he’s also heartless in general...


