 Chapter 1 .9

Zhou Yunsheng was taking a bath, when a strong body suddenly came up behind him, and his slightly rough palms wandered around his waist and abdomen, slowly exploring downwards. ......

He let out a moving moan, enjoying himself while asking intermittently, "You sold, shares, to him?"

"Uh-huh."The man gasped for breath, couldn't wait to attack the city, his lips gripped the back of his lover's long, white neck and sucked and grinded it, unable to stop.

"Well ......," Zhou Yunsheng stifled a grunt and mocked, "Selling a bunch of scrap paper to your nephew at a sky-high price, you can be a really good uncle."

"It is precisely because of being good to him that I sold it to him.He's had too smooth a ride and needs to learn to face setbacks.Otherwise, when the next time someone else strikes, he will most likely fall flat on his face and never be able to stand up again."

Zhou Yunsheng concentrated on enjoying himself and did not reply.As the protagonist of this world, Zhou Wenjing had naturally experienced ups and downs, but had survived them all with the help of Du Hulang and his many lovers.Du Hulang's tolerance towards him could be said to be unprincipled, where as now, knowing that there was a trap in front of him he still watched him jump into it, and even pushed him in the back.

The people surrounding Zhou Wenjing had changed and indirectly changed the world.Zhou Yunsheng narrowed his eyes and stared at the Smart Brain on his wrist that only he could see, hooking his lips in satisfaction.The progress bar in the upper left corner of the Think Brain had risen to 75%, not far from the booked target.

-------------------------------------

The two brothers of the Zhou family fought to the death, but the eldest son of the Zhou family was silent, and while the outside world sighed in admiration for Zhou Wenjing's rise, they also sighed at the eldest son's incompetence.If not for the mediocre ability of the eldest son, the Zhou Family Group would not have fallen into the hands of two illegitimate children.
Yes, although Zhou Wenjing became the new president, but Zhou Wenang after all owns 30% of Zhou's shares, is still a major shareholder, even if there is no decision-making power, every year to eat the dividends can also live comfortably at ease.

This day, Zhou Wenjing prepared to convene the first shareholders meeting since taking office, all have been present.The tall and beautiful secretary handed him the speech, and her fingertips painted with bright red cardamom gently scratched on the back of his hand suggestively.

Zhou Wenjing's lower body tightened slightly, but his face did not show at all, glancing at the speech was about to speak, the door of the conference room opened, a uniformed police officer walked in, took out his ID and opened his mouth seriously, "Hello, I'm Xing Guoquan, head of the Commercial Crimes Investigation Section, please Mr. Zhou Wen'an, Mr. Lin Deyi, Mr. Zhou Shicong, Mr. Zhu Gang, Mr. Yang Ruxuan, Mr. He Hongbo, please follow me to the police station to investigate the case....... follow me to the police station for investigation."

He arrested eleven people in one breath, all of them were Zhou Group's major shareholders, and took away all the financial staff and company account books, and asked Zhou Wenjing to go to the police station to assist in the investigation.Such a big move led to an uproar both inside and outside the industry, and Zhou's stock, which had just appreciated due to the successful reorganization, began to fall furiously again.

Twenty-four hours later, Zhou Wenjing was released, only to realize that someone hacked Zhou Wen'ang and Zhou Hao's computer, got their bribes, tax evasion, money laundering, illegal financing and other criminal evidence, anonymously mailed it to the police.Due to the reason that the amount of money involved was particularly huge, the police department quickly set up a task force to investigate the Zhou Group.

If these crimes were established, Zhou would face a series of problems such as asset freezing, delisting, and huge fines, and in more serious cases, it would lead to bankruptcy.In order to get Zhou, Zhou Wenjing had invested more than a billion dollars, if Zhou collapsed, his painstakingly managed Zongda Group would also be implicated, once the stock plummeted, billions of dollars of assets would evaporate into thin air, and the competitors would rise up and attack Zongda, dividing it up.

Zhou was not a piece of fat meat, but a quagmire that would be difficult to get out of.This was the biggest crisis Zhou Wenjing had ever encountered since he started his career in business, he felt confused and even a little scared, unconsciously he started the car and drove towards Du Hulang's company.

"Uncle, you must help me."The speaking voice ended abruptly, and he stared at the two people in front of him in dismay.

Two people deep in the leather sofa, hands are holding a glass of wine, tall man was slender and long youth pressed below, red wine splashed on his white shirt, resulting in close to the skin of the fabric outlined a broad and strong chest, combed a meticulous hair is now very messy, lining his already handsome and peerless face more and more sex - sensual.

He wrapped one hand around the youth's supple and powerful waist, one hand steadied the wine glass, in the past always flashed a dangerous light in the eyes now only remaining strong love and infatuation.

The youth took a sip of the wine and hung his head to cross over, the bright red wine dripping down the lips of the two men as they rolled over and over, the picture was charming and beautiful.

Zhou Wenjing was shocked by this scene in his mind, straight after several minutes before he spoke with difficulty, "What is your relationship?"

"What kind of relationship do you think we have?"Zhou Yunsheng felt a little spoiled, biting his lover's lips before sitting up straight, tilting his head back to drink the red wine in one go, because of the love affair, the peach blossom eyes that were already seductive now appeared even more colorful and extraordinary.

Zhou Wenjing stared at Du Hulang, saw that he did not deny, only possessive tightly embraced the youth, in this moment, suddenly understood everything.To bring down a commercial giant like the Zhou Clan, 
there must be a much larger force behind it as a push.Just who hated Zhou to the extent that they intended to destroy it?And who could mobilize such a huge force?

He had been pondering these two questions earlier, and when he arrived at the office and saw the scene just now, the answers were already coming out.


"So it's you, Zhou Yunsheng.For the sake of revenge, you can even sell your body, how lowly.I don't know how Yang Xi feels when he knows in his grave."He sneered.

Seeing him irritate his lover with his dead mother, Du Xu Lang's already cold features condensed a layer of frost.Zhou Yunsheng, however, did not get angry, but instead stroked his palm and laughed, as if he had heard a very funny joke.

Zhou Wenjing was angered by his reaction and interrogated, "What are you laughing at?"

"I'm laughing that you don't know the heights of heaven.Put out the cigarette."

The last sentence was obviously addressed to Du Hulang, who was preparing to light his cigar.Du Hulang's hand holding the lighter froze, then naturally put it down, threw the cigar into the trash can, and raised his hands in a surrendering gesture.Such an ingratiating attitude stung Zhou Wenjing's eyes more and more as he sat down across from the two men, pulled out his checkbook and sneered, "How much are you selling it for?I'll give it to you.You don't mess with my uncle."

Zhou Yunsheng pursed his lips and smiled more and more gently, but Du Hulang was furious and snapped, "Inoue, have someone send Wenjing out!"


Inoue Hidayama who hid outside the door to watch the show had to step in, making two bodyguards to frame boss's cheap nephew out.The two were not related by blood, even with Zhou Wenjing's mother being a childhood playmate with deep feelings, but coming all the way to C country to take care of it, and also giving money and contacts to let him set up his own business, boss had already paid enough.

What qualifications does Zhou Wenjing have to intervene in boss's emotional problems?Sure enough, he was too good to him, so he was getting unaware of it ah!Inoue Hideyama glanced at the furious Zhou Wenjing and secretly shook his head.

"Young Jing, take a look at this."Inoue Hidetama sent the person to the downstairs hall and turned on the amplifier display hanging in the hall.

The charismatic face of the internationally renowned host, Lydia, leapt out and spoke a large paragraph in slightly French-accented English.Zhou Wenjing was immediately captured with all his heart and soul, this turned out to be an exclusive interview with the president of Noah Group on cbs, the most famous channel in a country.Because he had returned to country c and was busy acquiring Zhou, he had surprisingly not been able to see it.

What kind of person is the president of Noah Group?He started his business from selling small software, at first, the registered fund of Noah Group was only a mere 400,000 dollars, but after just one and a half years, he created 400 million dollars of profit and successfully listed on the stock market.Noah Group is very young, so far this year, only the sixth anniversary of the establishment, but squeezed out many old plutocrats, ranked first in the world's top 100.The president of Noah Group acts extremely low-key, never appear in the media, but this does not prevent people from worshiping him.

He was the idol of the young generation of self-employed entrepreneurs, and the myths he created were unbreakable.Conceited as Zhou Wenjing, he also had to recognize the other party's toughness.

But what did he see?He actually saw Zhou Yunsheng's face on the screen!How was this possible!

“It turns out that the famous Deicide is actually Mr. Zhou,” Lydia said, looking very surprised, and immediately asked sharply, “Did you participate in the competition hosted by your own company and win first place with a brilliant performance because you had prior access to the copy materials? What you did is unfair to the other participants.”

So Deicide is him? Zhou Wenjing was utterly shocked. The intense battle to acquire Qing Shui Warehouse was so spectacular that the game video, once released, was revered by many business professionals as a textbook of business warfare. Every detail was repeatedly studied and analyzed. As a result, Deicide was elevated to the status of a god for his far-sighted business vision and decisive investment strategies. Everyone was curious about what kind of person could possess such extraordinary abilities and what his real identity was.

It turns out he is the CEO of Noah Global. Yes, he must have gotten the internal information in advance. All that talk about strategic brilliance and winning from a distance—it's all fake. He cheated! Zhou Wenjing refused to acknowledge his crushing defeat in their first encounter.

The Zhou Yunsheng on the screen smiled slightly, “I swear to God, I didn’t receive any information. My conditions were the same as all the other contestants’. I thought that the Noah Group behind me should be enough to demonstrate my strength.”

Lydia was taken aback, awkwardly smiling. Indeed, he developed Noah Group into such a massive enterprise in his early twenties. He led an era and changed people's lives. Just sitting here was enough to represent everything.

After that, Zhou Wenjing lost interest in continuing the interview. When he was feeling smug about the first money he earned, when he was proud of the brilliance of Zongda Group, Zhou Yunsheng had already left him far behind. He was someone who could stand on equal footing with high-ranking figures like Du Xulang, while Zhou Wenjing took secret pleasure in being addressed respectfully as “Jing Shao.” He even thought that the other person might betray him for the sake of the small Zhou family company and try to humiliate him with money.

Noah Group is a multinational company with annual profits in the billions, and Zhou Yunsheng would probably not even bother to bend down and pick up a check worth a few million if it dropped on the floor.

Such a gap, such a gap… it’s an immense difference…

Zhou Wenjing couldn’t find the words to describe his shame, and when he saw Inoue Hideyama squinting at him, his face turned red. He fled as if running away.


