Chapter 1.10

The Zhou family group ultimately collapsed. This massive business ship, a long-established family that had stood for nearly a century, was reduced to ashes in just two months. And Zongda Group was inevitably implicated, with its stock price plummeting, commercial crime investigations piling up, and competitors launching a full-scale attack and suppression. All of this was enough to leave Zhou Wenjing at his wit's end.

Zhou Yunsheng stared at the intelligent wristband on his wrist, the progress bar reaching 99%. Because of the change in the original owner’s fate, this world was about to slip out of the main god’s control, heading down an unpredictable path.

There was still 1% chance to bring it back to the starting point, but Zhou Yunsheng didn’t mind. He could choose how long to stay in this world, so he had enough time to push the process forward.

Half a month ago, CBS's interview with the CEO of Noah Group was aired on C-National’s international news channel, and the true identity of this legendary figure was finally revealed. Meanwhile, the Yang family, which had been severely damaged and on the brink of bankruptcy, quickly rose to the ranks of C-National’s top families thanks to this opportunity.

Today was the 60th birthday of Mrs. Guo Lindanping, the wife of the Guo family head, Guo Liqian. As in-laws of the Guo family, the head of the Yang family, Yang Zhenhai, and his wife were invited to attend. Of course, the main purpose of the Guo family was to get acquainted with Zhou Yunsheng through the Yang family, as Yang Zhenhai was Zhou Yunsheng’s maternal uncle, and their relationship was very close.

According to the original fate, after the death of Zhou’s father, Zhou Wenjing and Zhou Wen’ang would join forces to deal with the Yang family, and the Yang family would quickly fall apart. Because of this, the original Zhou Yunsheng didn’t receive the protection of his maternal family and lived a miserable life.

But now, the Yang family was no longer the same.

When the Yang family faced a capital withdrawal crisis, Yang Zhenhai’s wife, Guo Shufang, had gone back home for help but was rejected by Guo Liqian. Guo Liqian had married Guo Lindanping and fathered two daughters. Eager for a son, he kept a mistress who gave birth to twins—a boy and a girl—and brought them into the family to be raised, nearly causing Guo Lindanping to suffer a heart attack.

The elderly Guo family couple were desperate for grandchildren and, without considering the feelings of Guo Lindanping and her daughters, insisted on adding the twins to the family tree. Guo Liqian even took the twins everywhere with him, raising them so that, at just twenty years old, they had already entered the board of directors, clearly positioning them as the next head of the Guo family.

It was easy to imagine how awkward the position of Guo Shufang and her daughters was in the Guo family. When she came home to seek help, the elderly couple had softened, but the mistress and her children persuaded Guo Liqian to demand conditions from the Yang family, offering to take the sea tunnel project at the lowest price.

Such actions were no different from taking advantage of someone’s misfortune. Guo Shufang cried in anger but was helpless. In the end, it was Guo Lindanping and her younger daughter who sold their jewelry and secretly gave her tens of millions. This was why, after her nephew filled the financial gap, Guo Shufang went on a shopping spree, buying jewelry, just to make up for her mother and sister.

In short, without Mrs. Guo Lindanping, the Yang and Guo families would have long become enemies.

Although Guo Lindanping was already sixty, she maintained herself very well. Her figure was full and her complexion rosy, exuding a peaceful beauty that came with the passage of time. Guo Liqian stood beside her, smiling and greeting the guests.

“The Yang family’s car has arrived.” Upon seeing the luxury car slowly approaching the gate, Guo Liqian’s eyes brightened. He quickly stepped forward with the twins. Guo Lindanping, supported by her younger daughter, followed at a slow pace, a hint of sarcasm curling at the corner of her mouth.

Yang Zhenhai and his wife walked along with a young man. The young man was handsome, with a gentle demeanor. His most striking feature was his long, almond-shaped eyes that seemed both indifferent and full of emotion when he looked at people, leaving an unforgettable impression.

“This must be your eldest nephew, right? Truly a fine young man!” Guo Liqian greeted warmly, trying to introduce the twins to the young man.

Zhou Yunsheng smiled faintly, nodded, and bypassed the three, taking Guo Lindanping’s hand and wishing her, “Happy birthday, Grandma.” His gesture clearly indicated who he was closer to.

“Why are you standing here? Come inside.” Guo Shufang affectionately linked arms with her nephew and mother and led them inside. Guo Liqian, feeling awkward, didn’t let the opportunity slip, leading the twins to follow closely behind. Their arrival caused all the guests to turn their heads and secretly praise the Guo family for marrying into such a good family.

“Yunsheng, let me introduce you. This is your cousin, Guo Zinan, who is currently learning under me. If you have time, you can teach him a few things. This is your cousin, Guo Baoyi, who is still studying vocal music at B University.” Guo Liqian persistently pushed the twins toward the young man.

Guo Baoyi smiled brightly and gracefully, while Guo Zinan frowned, his eyes filled with hostility.

Zhou Yunsheng glanced at him and smiled, “I heard you’re good friends with Wen’ang?”

Now, who didn’t know about the feud between the Zhou family’s three brothers? It was originally thought that the two illegitimate sons of the Zhou family had driven the legitimate eldest son to the edge of no return, but who could have predicted that the eldest son turned out to be an untouchable tyrant, easily crushing the Zhou family and leaving the two illegitimate sons in ruins.

Thus, no matter how handsome or gentle Zhou Yunsheng appeared, people couldn’t ignore his decisive and ruthless methods.

Thinking of this, Guo Zinan's face turned slightly pale, and Guo Liqun awkwardly interrupted, "He's still young, his horizons are narrow, so it's inevitable he might make some poor choices in friends. There's a saying, young people's mistakes are always forgivable."

Zhou Yunsheng smiled even more gently and commented, "Young people have the right to make mistakes, but not every mistake is worth forgiving. Mr. Guo, to be blunt, you should be stricter with the younger generation and not indulge their mistakes. Otherwise, they might end up like my younger brother Wen Ang, who didn't get out of prison until he was fifty, and by then, he had no chance to start over. Don’t you agree?"

On the surface, the Zhou family group collapsed due to involvement in a series of economic crimes, but secretly, who didn’t know it was the hand of the Zhou family's eldest son? This man could crush a giant like the Zhou family with just a snap of his fingers, and a third-rate family like the Guos wouldn't even last one round with him.

Guo Zinan’s body trembled uncontrollably, and Guo Liqun awkwardly nodded, wiping the cold sweat from his forehead with a handkerchief. Guo Lindanping and her daughter continued to chat and drink casually, seemingly oblivious, but secretly pleased.

Just then, a series of surprised exclamations came from the door. The Guo family turned their heads to see a tall man walking in. He wore a perfectly tailored black suit, with a silver-gray handkerchief in his breast pocket. His hair was combed back, revealing a sharply chiseled face, and his narrow, sharp eyes made him appear intimidating.

The Du family had now risen to become the world’s leading arms dealer. After consolidating power, all forces were under Du Xulang’s control, and fewer people could pose a threat to him. Over the years, he had gradually emerged in the public eye.

In C country, most people had heard of his deeds. Although Guo Liqun couldn’t understand why such a prominent figure would show up uninvited, he immediately put down his wine glass and went to greet him, enjoying the envious gazes from the crowd.

However, Du Xulang bypassed him and walked straight towards the smiling young man, opening his arms. "Baby, why didn’t you wait for me?"

"I was out buying a birthday gift with Auntie." Zhou Yunsheng hugged him, then handed him his wine glass and grabbed another one for himself.

"Happy birthday, Grandma." After releasing his partner, Du Xulang gently hugged Mrs. Guo Lindanping. The affectionate address made her momentarily stunned.

"Mr. Du, you and Yunsheng are..."

"He’s my boyfriend." Zhou Yunsheng casually dropped a bombshell, causing Du Xulang to laugh in delight. He absolutely loved his partner’s boldness and straightforwardness. If you didn’t even have the courage to admit your love, how could you move forward together?

Guo Lindanping, not being a fool, quickly regained her composure, realizing her daughter had probably already known about it. On the other hand, Guo Liqun and the other two people turned pale and quickly excused themselves. With the Noah Group already making waves, adding the Du family’s financial power, this couple seemed to be the strongest combination in the world. Anyone who provoked them was bound to face dire consequences.

Thinking back to how they had ganged up on the Yang family, Guo Liqun deeply regretted it, cursing the mistress nearby and wishing he could slap her to death.

The onlookers, realizing that the Du family and Noah Global were about to cooperate on new weapon developments, suddenly had an epiphany—so the Guo family was just riding the coattails of the Yang family after all.

Not long after, Zhou Wenjing walked in, holding a pure-looking young girl. Now, after facing repeated setbacks, the Zongda Group was far from its former glory, and he no longer received the same attention as before. People simply referred to him as "young and accomplished." With Zhou Yunsheng holding the reins, what could his talents do?

Seeing the intimate drinking couple, Zhou Wenjing’s gaze darkened, while the young girl beside him shot a hateful glance.

"Isn't that your second uncle’s daughter?" Zhou Yunsheng gently swirled his wine.

The girl was one of Zhou Wenjing's many lovers, and her family background was quite complicated. Her father was Du Xulang’s second uncle, once the most likely to inherit the Du family’s fortune, but was suppressed by Du Xulang. The two had clashed many times, and their animosity ran deep, each wishing to destroy the other.

By openly dating this woman, Zhou Wenjing was effectively taking the opposing side to Du Xulang.

Du Xulang stared at him and saw that his nephew only nodded coldly, his attitude indifferent. He suddenly chuckled. "It’s my fault. I spoiled him too much."

If things had gone according to their original course, Du Xulang would have easily forgiven his nephew, only to be stabbed by the girl. Zhou Wenjing killed the girl’s father to avenge his uncle, and their bond actually grew closer, not more distant.

Now that Du Xulang had a lover, his desire for family ties naturally faded. Furthermore, Zhou Wenjing wasn’t even his blood relative. What did that make him? He had tricked Zhou Wenjing before, but also helped him stabilize the situation. If it weren’t for the Du family’s protection, the Zongda Group would have already been divided up.

Du Xulang felt he had already done enough for his nephew. He was no saint and wouldn’t tolerate endless indulgence. Since his nephew had shown he was ready to part ways, Du Xulang wouldn’t try to stop him.

Thinking this, Du Xulang raised his glass and drank it in one go.

Zhou Yunsheng was surprised to find that the progress bar on his smart brain had already reached 100%. After a brief moment of thought, he found the reason.

Du Xulang was Zhou Wenjing’s greatest "golden finger." The combined influence of all his women didn’t compare to Du Xulang alone. With Du Xulang’s backing, Zhou Wenjing could escape from all kinds of crises. Now that Du Xulang had withdrawn his protection, it would be much harder for him to get out of future trouble and reach his original goals.

Changing the protagonist’s fate was a shortcut to changing the world’s trajectory, but unless the protagonist was detrimental to him, Zhou Yunsheng would not actively provoke him. Zhou Wenjing’s downfall was due to him falling into the trap himself. Besides changing the protagonist’s fate, Zhou Yunsheng could also destroy the main system by changing history, technology, and even the fate of supporting characters.

He didn’t necessarily have to clash directly with the protagonist.

But undeniably, Du Xulang’s decision had saved him a lot of time and avoided many troubles. In a very good mood, Zhou Yunsheng looped his arm around Du Xulang’s neck and kissed his side cheek. "Thank you, darling. You've really helped me."

Du Xulang was momentarily stunned, then reacted quickly, pressing his hand to the back of Zhou Yunsheng’s head, exchanging a passionate kiss, and secretly slipping a ring onto his left-hand ring finger.

The guests were stunned, and several of them even gasped. The next day, rumors about the two business giants spread everywhere, but neither side’s PR teams stepped forward to clarify.


